June 7, 1931

P. L. Sperr

Bay Street, at Edgewater Street, viewing south from near Townsend Avenue. Shown are operations on railroad crossing elimination. Note, in the left background, the Pouch Terminal and the Wrigley plant.

P. L. Sperr

Bay Street, at its junction with Edgewater Street, showing construction work in progress on grade crossing elimination. The Staten Island Railroad crosses the street at this point. The view is northward. Note the old tracks in the foreground and the concrete supports for the new bridge.
